<% content_for :title, "Managing Slots — Admin Manual" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Admin Manual", path: admin_docs_path },
      { label: "Slots", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Managing Slots</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">Slots are the 1-hour blocks customers book. You control the schedule entirely.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-stone-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Creating a Single Slot</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            Go to <strong>Slots → New Slot</strong>. Pick a date and start time, then click
            <strong>Create Slot</strong>. The slot is immediately available for customers to book.
          </p>
          <p>
            Creating a slot automatically emails any customers on the
            <%= link_to "waitlist", admin_waitlist_entries_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-900" %>
            if there are pending entries and the new slot falls within the next 30 days.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Creating Slots in Bulk</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            Go to <strong>Slots → Bulk Create</strong>. This is the fastest way to set up your schedule:
          </p>
          <ol class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-decimal pl-5">
            <li>Choose which <strong>days of the week</strong> to include (e.g., Tuesday, Wednesday, Friday)</li>
            <li>Set a <strong>date range</strong> (e.g., March 1 through March 31)</li>
            <li>Set a <strong>time window</strong> (e.g., 10:00 AM to 6:00 PM)</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Create Slots</strong></li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            The app generates one slot per hour within the time window, on each selected day, across
            the entire date range. It skips any slots that already exist. You'll see a summary of
            how many were created.
          </p>
          <p>
            If any slots were created successfully, the system automatically notifies customers on the
            <%= link_to "waitlist", admin_waitlist_entries_path, class: "underline hover:text-stone-900" %>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Overnight Sessions</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            If your studio runs late-night hours that span midnight (e.g., 10 PM to 2 AM), just set the
            end time earlier than the start time in Bulk Create — the app handles the midnight crossover
            automatically.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Cancelling a Slot</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            From the <strong>Slots</strong> list, click <strong>Cancel</strong> next to any open slot.
            Cancelled slots disappear from the customer calendar immediately.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can only cancel slots that haven't been reserved. If a slot is part of a booking,
            cancel the booking first (which releases the slots) and then cancel the individual slots
            if needed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Bulk Cancelling Slots</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            To remove many open slots at once, use the checkboxes on the <strong>Slots</strong> list:
          </p>
          <ol class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-decimal pl-5">
            <li>Check the box next to each slot you want to cancel, or use the checkbox in the table header to select all visible open slots at once</li>
            <li>A red action bar appears showing how many slots are selected</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Cancel Selected</strong> and confirm the prompt</li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            Only open slots can be bulk-cancelled. Held or reserved slots are skipped automatically,
            even if their checkboxes were somehow included.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
